WEBVTT

00:07.240 --> 00:09.208
[ echoing distorted voices ]

00:09.210 --> 00:12.211
Dispatcher:
<i>911. What's your emergency?</i>

00:12.213 --> 00:14.279
John: <i>My -- my daughter is --</i>
<i>[</i> <i>clears throat</i> ]

00:14.281 --> 00:17.516
<i>My daughter</i>
<i>hasn't come home.</i>

00:17.518 --> 00:18.884
<i>I-it's not like her</i>
<i>to stay out this late.</i>

00:18.886 --> 00:20.352
<i>How old</i>
<i>is your daughter?</i>

00:20.354 --> 00:22.554
<i>She's 13.</i>
<i>She's only 13.</i>

00:22.556 --> 00:25.457
<i>And when</i>
<i>was she last seen?</i>
<i>What time</i>
<i>did this call come in?</i>

00:25.459 --> 00:27.359
Last night --
two minutes after midnight.
<i>She called my wife, her mom,</i>
<i>to get a ride home,</i>

00:27.361 --> 00:29.995
<i>And then</i>
<i>she wasn't there.</i>
<i>We responded immediately.</i>

00:29.997 --> 00:31.330
<i>We've called her friends.</i>

00:31.332 --> 00:32.865
<i>We've looked everywhere</i>
<i>for her.</i>

00:34.701 --> 00:36.969
Where was your daughter
last seen?

00:36.971 --> 00:39.238
John: Well, she called from
the mall, wanting a ride home,

00:39.240 --> 00:41.507
But when my wife went to
pick her up, she wasn't there.

00:41.509 --> 00:42.908
Sykes:
And where's your wife now?

00:42.910 --> 00:45.511
Mom's out driving around,
looking for michelle.

00:45.513 --> 00:48.013
John: <i>And -- and she was --</i>
<i>she had a bully.</i>

00:48.015 --> 00:49.748
<i>This kid at the mall --</i>
<i>he bullied her last weekend.</i>

00:49.750 --> 00:51.050
Dispatcher: <i>She was bullied?</i>
<i>Yes!</i>

00:51.052 --> 00:52.751
<i>This kid</i>
<i>and his friends --</i>

00:52.753 --> 00:53.685
<i>They followed her</i>
<i>into the bathroom last week,</i>

00:53.687 --> 00:55.387
<i>And they assaulted her.</i>

00:55.389 --> 00:57.890
You told the 911 operator
that your daughter was bullied?

00:57.892 --> 01:00.592
Yeah, last weekend
at the, um, at the same mall.

01:00.594 --> 01:02.261
This bully --
he got a group of boys together,

01:02.263 --> 01:03.695
Trapped her
in the bathroom

01:03.697 --> 01:07.199
[sighs] pulled down her pants,
and took pictures.

01:07.201 --> 01:09.001
We don't call that bullying,
mr. Brand.

01:09.003 --> 01:10.836
We call that
sexual battery of a minor.

01:10.838 --> 01:12.271
Flynn:
Why didn't you report that?

01:12.273 --> 01:14.039
Because
michelle begged us not to.

01:14.041 --> 01:16.041
She -- she didn't want
to draw any more
attention to herself.

01:16.043 --> 01:19.511
She already feels
ostracized enough as it is.
And why is that?

01:19.513 --> 01:22.247
Dispatcher: <i>Does she have any</i>
<i>defining tattoos or birthmarks?</i>

01:22.249 --> 01:23.849
John: <i>No, no, no, no.</i>
<i>She's a tomboy.</i>

01:23.851 --> 01:25.384
<i>Just tell the police</i>
<i>to look for a tomboy</i>

01:25.386 --> 01:28.187
<i>In a white skirt and pink top,</i>
<i>I think.</i>

01:31.891 --> 01:34.426
Is michelle...
A boy?

01:34.428 --> 01:36.695
She used to be michael.

01:36.697 --> 01:38.697
Now she's michelle.

01:42.869 --> 01:46.138
How long ago
did this transition begin?

01:46.140 --> 01:47.873
Well, she was diagnosed
with gender identity disorder

01:47.875 --> 01:49.308
In the first grade.

01:49.310 --> 01:51.777
Sykes: Other than
last week at the mall,

01:51.779 --> 01:54.046
Has anyone else
attacked michelle

01:54.048 --> 01:55.881
Or taken pictures of her?
No,
she was teased a lot,

01:55.883 --> 01:57.716
But that was the first time
that anybody ever hurt her.

01:57.718 --> 01:59.084
Any chance
she ran away?

01:59.086 --> 02:00.285
John:
No. No, no, no.

02:00.287 --> 02:01.720
Flynn: Was your daughter
depressed?

02:01.722 --> 02:03.989
Did she ever talk about
hurting herself?

02:03.991 --> 02:06.325
No, look, I already told you
that I was worried

02:06.327 --> 02:07.926
That damn boy at the mall
might have attacked her.

02:07.928 --> 02:09.628
I mean, that's why
she called home for a ride,

02:09.630 --> 02:12.231
Because she saw him again,
and she got scared.

02:12.233 --> 02:14.066
I mean, maybe she's running away
from him.

02:14.068 --> 02:16.268
Dispatcher: <i>Can you describe</i>
<i>this young man?</i>

02:16.270 --> 02:18.804
John:
[  <i>scoffs</i>] <i>look, I wish I could,</i>
<i>but I've never seen him.</i>

02:18.806 --> 02:20.305
Okay,
what's his name?

02:20.307 --> 02:22.007
John:
Uh, he doesn't go to her school.

02:22.009 --> 02:23.108
I don't know.

02:23.110 --> 02:24.443
I can get his screen name.

02:24.445 --> 02:25.844
Those pictures
from the mall bathroom --

02:25.846 --> 02:28.147
He posted them.
Why didn't you
tell me that?

02:28.149 --> 02:29.781
Michelle didn't want you
to know.

02:29.783 --> 02:31.250
I'm so sorry.

02:31.252 --> 02:33.018
I would have told you,
but she was so embarrassed.

02:33.020 --> 02:36.922
Oh, my god, you did it?
You called the police?

02:36.924 --> 02:38.090
John: What did you
expect me to do?

02:38.092 --> 02:40.159
John,
you're overreacting.

02:40.161 --> 02:41.960
She's been missing
since 7:00.
She's probably
at a friend's house.

02:41.962 --> 02:44.096
No, I already called
all of her friends.

02:44.098 --> 02:45.697
Look,
I can't just sit here.
Shh. Excuse me.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.499
Is this
michelle's computer?

02:48.935 --> 02:50.469
May we take a look
at it?

02:50.471 --> 02:51.970
Yes, of course.

02:51.972 --> 02:54.439
Tao: Finally.
"mr. T -- the tranny hunter --

02:54.441 --> 02:57.176
"has sent your male junk
to every e-mail, facebook,

02:57.178 --> 02:59.244
And web link you have."
matt:
Can you click on "junk"?

03:01.447 --> 03:03.215
Ugh.

03:03.217 --> 03:04.816
Oh, my god.

03:04.818 --> 03:07.653
<i>Freaking tranny, huh?</i>
<i>Oh, look at this.</i>

03:07.655 --> 03:09.555
<i>What are you doing</i>
<i>in the girls' bathroom, kiddo?</i>

03:09.557 --> 03:11.557
<i>What are you doing here?</i>
<i>You think you're a girl, huh?</i>

03:11.559 --> 03:13.392
<i>Girls don't have this,</i>
<i>do they?</i>

03:13.394 --> 03:14.960
<i>Ohh,</i>
<i>girls don't have that, huh?</i>

03:14.962 --> 03:16.828
[ <i>laughter</i> ]

03:16.830 --> 03:20.465
Who's seen this? How many people
has he sent this to?

03:20.467 --> 03:22.067
These pictures
have probably gone viral.

03:22.069 --> 03:25.070
You see, this is exactly why
she wanted to change schools.

03:25.072 --> 03:26.371
What are we supposed
to do --

03:26.373 --> 03:27.973
Sell our house,
uproot our family

03:27.975 --> 03:29.541
In the middle of matt's
senior year of high school?

03:29.543 --> 03:31.043
That's insane.

03:31.045 --> 03:32.878
No, the harassment of
our daughter is what's insane.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.179
Anne:
Oh, my god.

03:34.181 --> 03:36.415
We have turned our lives
upside down

03:36.417 --> 03:38.083
To accommodate that child.

03:38.085 --> 03:40.085
What else do you want
from us?

03:40.087 --> 03:41.887
John: Look, what do you
expect her to do --

03:41.889 --> 03:44.022
Go back to school after
that's all over the internet?

03:44.024 --> 03:45.424
[ door slams ]

03:45.426 --> 03:46.925
Is there any way

03:46.927 --> 03:48.360
You can take those pictures
of the kid offline?

03:48.362 --> 03:50.095
I'm working on it, andy,
but our bully is hiding

03:50.097 --> 03:52.064
Behind a moderately
sophisticated proxy server,

03:52.066 --> 03:55.434
And I need him to log on
so I can trace his I.P.

03:55.436 --> 03:56.902
Provenza: Well, there's a large,
wooded park

03:56.904 --> 03:58.237
Between the house
and the mall.

03:58.239 --> 03:59.771
Sharon: If our missing child
walked home

03:59.773 --> 04:01.340
Or tried
to get away from somebody,

04:01.342 --> 04:02.908
It'd be
a likely place to hide.

04:02.910 --> 04:05.744
Well, I need evidence dogs
to search the park --

04:05.746 --> 04:08.447
As many as I can get.
One second, lieutenant.
Don't hang up.

04:08.449 --> 04:11.683
How long since
the child was last seen?

04:11.685 --> 04:14.453
15 hours --
since 7:00 last night.

04:14.455 --> 04:17.856
Okay, let's call it
a critical missing.

04:17.858 --> 04:20.292
Give provenza
all the resources he needs.

04:20.294 --> 04:21.426
Thank you, chief.

04:21.428 --> 04:23.629
Just find her...
Or him...

04:23.631 --> 04:25.364
Or whoever he is.

04:28.768 --> 04:31.236
I want
a 40-block grid search.

04:31.238 --> 04:33.472
Half your guys start at the mall
where she was last seen.

04:33.474 --> 04:35.107
The other half
start right here.

04:35.109 --> 04:36.975
Am I supposed to tell them
to look for a boy or a girl?

04:36.977 --> 04:39.211
Birth certificate
says male.

04:39.213 --> 04:41.146
Well,
a lot's changed since then.

04:41.148 --> 04:42.948
Just find the kid alive,
okay?

04:42.950 --> 04:44.483
John:
You know, when, um,

04:44.485 --> 04:46.451
When michelle was still
in diapers, and I kid you not,

04:46.453 --> 04:48.420
She used to correct us
if we called her a boy.

04:48.422 --> 04:51.590
He'd say,
"god made a mistake.

04:51.592 --> 04:56.128
He gave me the wrong body,
mommy."

04:56.130 --> 04:57.796
John: We fought it
for years.

04:57.798 --> 05:00.732
I mean, you know, took away
toys that were feminine,

05:00.734 --> 05:02.100
Dressed her like a boy.

05:02.102 --> 05:04.102
Nothing worked.

05:04.104 --> 05:05.804
Excuse me, folks.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.773
Um,
we need some unwashed items

05:07.775 --> 05:10.075
From michelle's
laundry basket --

05:10.077 --> 05:12.911
Something the dogs
can get a scent from.

05:14.180 --> 05:15.347
[ computer beeps ]

05:15.349 --> 05:16.415
He's logged on.
I have him.

05:17.950 --> 05:19.084
I have our bully.

05:19.086 --> 05:21.053
Lewis gates.

05:22.522 --> 05:25.390
Woman: Coming!

05:26.659 --> 05:27.993
Hello, mrs. Gates.

05:27.995 --> 05:29.127
Can I help you?

05:29.129 --> 05:30.762
Is lewis here?

05:32.532 --> 05:34.433
L.A.P.D.! Stop!

05:41.307 --> 05:43.275
