John:
Is there, uh, any news yet?

13:15.629 --> 13:17.162
Any news at all?

13:17.164 --> 13:19.164
I'll let you know
the minute we confirm something.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.131
Thank you.

13:20.133 --> 13:21.266
Mm-hmm.

13:21.268 --> 13:22.801
Uh, right this way.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.340
Okay, so,
michelle called the house

13:29.342 --> 13:30.975
A few minutes after 7:00
last night,

13:30.977 --> 13:32.343
Wanting a ride home
from the mall.

13:32.345 --> 13:33.344
What happened next?

13:33.346 --> 13:35.113
First I chewed her out

13:35.115 --> 13:36.848
Because she wasn't
supposed to be at the mall,

13:36.850 --> 13:38.917
And then I put the dinner
in the oven,

13:38.919 --> 13:40.685
And I got in the car
to go get her.

13:40.687 --> 13:41.953
You were home, too?

13:41.955 --> 13:43.488
I was watching
the dodgers game.

13:43.490 --> 13:45.190
I should have gone to the mall
with mom, but...

13:45.192 --> 13:48.359
When I got to the mall,
michelle didn't come out.

13:48.361 --> 13:50.528
I-I waited.
I tried her cell.

13:50.530 --> 13:53.865
I-I figured that
she caught a ride with somebody.

13:53.867 --> 13:55.700
I wish I had
gone in to look for her.

13:55.702 --> 13:57.368
I should have
gone in the mall.

13:57.370 --> 13:59.304
And you, mr. Brand?

13:59.306 --> 14:02.507
Just stuck
on the 101 freeway.

14:02.509 --> 14:05.310
And what time
did you get home?

14:05.312 --> 14:09.647
Um, 8:30 or 9:00.
I don't know.

14:09.649 --> 14:11.382
You know, by then
I'd already talked to annie,

14:11.384 --> 14:12.884
And she told me
michelle was missing.

14:12.886 --> 14:14.152
We all just
started to panic.

14:14.154 --> 14:15.720
Oh, my god,
that's him!

14:15.722 --> 14:17.455
Matt. Wait, matt!
That asshole
killed my sister!

14:17.457 --> 14:20.191
Hey, asshole, what'd you do
to my sister, huh?

14:20.193 --> 14:23.361
Anne: Matthew!
Son of a bitch!

14:23.363 --> 14:24.963
John: Matt! Matthew!

14:24.965 --> 14:26.564
Matthew!
Get up here!

14:26.566 --> 14:28.499
Lewis: Get off me!

14:28.501 --> 14:30.201
Sykes: Stop!
John: Matthew!

14:30.203 --> 14:32.904
Go!

14:32.906 --> 14:35.740
Go! Go!
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

14:35.742 --> 14:38.810
What are you doing?
Let's go.

14:43.082 --> 14:45.650
[ police radio chatter ]

14:47.553 --> 14:50.154
The victim's cellphone
run out of juice?

14:50.156 --> 14:52.757
Battery's missing.

14:52.759 --> 14:56.227
[ cellphone beeps ]

14:56.229 --> 14:58.429
[ cellphone vibrates ]
sykes.

14:58.431 --> 15:00.198
Provenza: Yes, I want you
to go to the victim's house.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.933
Bring a few boxes.

15:01.935 --> 15:05.370
Go through their bedrooms,
gather all their shoes,

15:05.372 --> 15:08.006
And, sykes?
Yes, sir?

15:08.008 --> 15:12.610
I want you to bag them
and tag them separately.

15:12.612 --> 15:14.846
Dr. Morales: There were no signs
of sexual abuse.

15:15.881 --> 15:17.482
Thank god.

15:18.751 --> 15:19.884
Is it possible
that he was under a lot of --

15:19.886 --> 15:21.753
She.
Let's stick with "she."

15:21.755 --> 15:24.856
It helps me to identify
with the victim, okay?

15:24.858 --> 15:26.224
Okay.

15:26.226 --> 15:27.959
It sounds like
this child

15:27.961 --> 15:30.228
Was in an extremely
stressful situation.

15:30.230 --> 15:32.196
Is it possible
that she committed suicide?

15:32.198 --> 15:33.865
And then
buried herself?

15:33.867 --> 15:35.733
Lawyers.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.735
I'm writing down homicide,
rios.

15:37.737 --> 15:39.470
The murder weapon
appears to be

15:39.472 --> 15:42.040
Something like
a heavy length of pipe,

15:42.042 --> 15:43.408
Only tapered at the end.

15:43.410 --> 15:45.610
See how the wounds
go from narrow to wider?

15:45.612 --> 15:48.646
You're describing a bat.

15:48.648 --> 15:50.248
Oh, god.

15:50.250 --> 15:52.717
An aluminum bat --
could be.

15:52.719 --> 15:56.054
She's running.
She looks back.

15:56.056 --> 15:57.922
The bat swings
to the side of the head.

15:57.924 --> 16:00.124
She falls to her knees.
The bat swings again.

16:00.126 --> 16:05.196
And one last time...
Just to make certain.

16:07.166 --> 16:09.000
Poor kid.

16:09.002 --> 16:13.104
This kind of thing --
I can't get used to it.

16:13.106 --> 16:16.007
Let's hope we never do.

16:16.009 --> 16:21.346
Captain, do you have
a suspect in custody?

16:21.348 --> 16:24.916
Yes, but I have issues
with charging him.

16:24.918 --> 16:26.584
You have to,
or you have to let him go.

16:26.586 --> 16:27.986
He's a juvenile.

16:27.988 --> 16:29.487
We can't keep him
more than eight hours.

16:29.489 --> 16:31.589
I'd like to hold him
a little longer than that, emma.

16:31.591 --> 16:33.791
How much longer?
Two or three years.

16:33.793 --> 16:36.794
Lewis has confessed
to sexual battery.

16:36.796 --> 16:38.830
And distributing lewd pictures
of a minor.

16:38.832 --> 16:41.966
But his behavior
and his personality

16:41.968 --> 16:43.701
Are inconsistent
with our victim's burial.

16:43.703 --> 16:46.170
If you look at the crime scene
where we found michelle...

16:46.172 --> 16:48.139
Somebody who cared about her
did this.

16:48.141 --> 16:51.542
[ inhales deeply ]
so, the brother or the father?

16:51.544 --> 16:53.144
Excuse me, captain.

16:53.146 --> 16:54.812
I just wanted to report

16:54.814 --> 16:56.280
That I bagged and tagged all
the shoes in the victim's house

16:56.282 --> 16:58.049
And took them to the lab
to be processed.

16:58.051 --> 16:59.484
Thank you, detective.

16:59.486 --> 17:02.153
Thank you.

17:02.155 --> 17:05.289
Buzz, wire up
detective sykes and myself

17:05.291 --> 17:07.392
With video cameras,
please.

17:07.394 --> 17:09.027
I want to document
this family's reaction

17:09.029 --> 17:12.363
When we give them
the death notification.

17:12.365 --> 17:14.665
Sykes:
I'm afraid we have bad news.

17:14.667 --> 17:15.733
[ sighs ]

17:15.735 --> 17:16.834
Oh, god.

17:16.836 --> 17:18.469
Oh, no.

17:18.471 --> 17:21.539
Sharon:
We found michelle's body

17:21.541 --> 17:23.041
Less than a mile
from your house.

17:23.043 --> 17:25.009
Anne: Oh, my god.

17:25.011 --> 17:26.477
This is not happening.

17:26.479 --> 17:28.513
You mean [clears throat]
you mean she's dead?

17:28.515 --> 17:29.547
Yes.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.315
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

17:31.317 --> 17:33.484
<i>We've confirmed it's her,</i>
<i>but while we're still</i>

17:33.486 --> 17:35.653
<i>Trying to make our case</i>
<i>against the murderer,</i>

17:35.655 --> 17:37.655
That's all I can tell you.

17:37.657 --> 17:40.658
Was it that monster?
Was it -- was it lewis?

17:40.660 --> 17:42.727
We are holding him,
but we can't say more than that.

17:44.496 --> 17:45.830
[ clears throat ]

17:45.832 --> 17:47.398
[ sniffles ]
I, uh...I want to see her body.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.434
Is that possible?
John, please.

17:49.436 --> 17:50.535
I want to see her,
okay?

17:50.537 --> 17:51.836
Look,
I-I have to see her.

17:51.838 --> 17:53.871
<i>Him --</i> you want to see him.
No, her.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.440
I said "her,"
and I meant "her"!

17:55.442 --> 17:57.442
For god's sake, john, I told you
that this would happen,

17:57.444 --> 17:58.910
And you wouldn't
listen to me.

17:58.912 --> 18:00.578
Are you happy now?

18:00.580 --> 18:02.580
Are you happy that you
bought him those dresses,

18:02.582 --> 18:03.881
That you gave him makeup,

18:03.883 --> 18:05.183
That you let him
grow his hair out?

18:05.185 --> 18:07.251
Mom.
And they're off.

18:07.253 --> 18:08.619
<i>I'm not having</i>
<i>this argument again.</i>

18:08.621 --> 18:10.254
You let him
pretend himself to death,

18:10.256 --> 18:11.889
And no one
could talk you out of it!

18:11.891 --> 18:14.225
Would you stop
blaming me?!

18:14.227 --> 18:16.360
Oh,
somebody's got a temper.

18:21.900 --> 18:25.136
I didn't --
I didn't make her what she was.

18:25.138 --> 18:27.805
Sorry to interrupt,
but to get out of your way

18:27.807 --> 18:30.475
And finish up our investigation
against lewis,

18:30.477 --> 18:32.243
We need to hear
your timeline again.

18:32.245 --> 18:34.245
Our times for what?
You already know who did this.

18:34.247 --> 18:36.114
Could you just listen
to someone else for a minute?

18:36.116 --> 18:38.616
Are you never tired
of getting it wrong?

18:38.618 --> 18:40.051
What --
what did I get wrong?

18:40.053 --> 18:41.552
If you'd only
stood up to him.

18:41.554 --> 18:43.254
Oh.
If you hadn't
encouraged him --

18:43.256 --> 18:45.056
I tried to accept her,
which is more than you ever did!

18:45.058 --> 18:46.591
[ voice breaking ]
look, what are you guys doing?

18:46.593 --> 18:48.159
Look, michelle is dead,

18:48.161 --> 18:50.495
So can you please
stop pretending

18:50.497 --> 18:52.096
That all of your arguments
are about her?

18:52.098 --> 18:53.531
You hate each other.
God!

18:59.404 --> 19:01.572
What's
the dad's alibi?

19:01.574 --> 19:03.074
Stuck in traffic.

19:03.076 --> 19:05.643
Let's see what's going on
in his finances.

19:06.778 --> 19:10.915
[ sighs ] even now, you're --
you're still calling her a boy.

19:10.917 --> 19:14.252
If you had only
backed me up.

19:15.754 --> 19:18.022
Sharon:
Excuse us, please.

19:18.024 --> 19:19.524
We'll leave you two
to talk this through.

19:19.526 --> 19:22.393
We're very sorry
for your loss.

19:24.997 --> 19:27.031
Captain?

19:27.033 --> 19:28.633
Wait.

19:28.635 --> 19:31.202
I have a right
to see my daughter's body.

19:31.204 --> 19:34.105
[ sighing ] oh.
Mr. Brand,
I don't think you understand.

19:34.107 --> 19:36.340
Your daughter
is at the morgue,

19:36.342 --> 19:39.043
And that is not a place
that you want to be right now.

19:39.045 --> 19:40.611
I promise you.

19:40.613 --> 19:45.016
I have the right to see her body
as a parent, don't I?

19:45.018 --> 19:47.885
<i>I want to see</i>
<i>my daughter's body.</i>

19:47.887 --> 19:50.121
Again?

19:54.560 --> 19:57.562
I want to see
my daughter's body!

20:03.402 --> 20:06.737
Jack: I think that transgender
kid was brave as hell.

20:06.739 --> 20:08.806
It took a lot of guts
to live in the open like that,

20:08.808 --> 20:12.043
And her father deserves credit
for having supported her.

20:12.045 --> 20:13.711
Her father
gave her dresses.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.880
He might as well have put
a target on the back

20:15.882 --> 20:17.415
That said, "beat me."

20:17.417 --> 20:19.584
She asked for those dresses,
and I still say brave kid.

20:19.586 --> 20:22.019
Besides,
it could be just as dangerous

20:22.021 --> 20:24.422
Pretending to be
somebody you're not.

20:24.424 --> 20:25.690
A lot of kids that
repress that kind of feeling

20:25.692 --> 20:27.158
End up killing themselves.

20:27.160 --> 20:29.493
You can't hide who you are,
as I'm sure you know.

20:32.998 --> 20:34.699
Sure I know what?

20:34.701 --> 20:38.135
Well,
as you know from...

20:39.838 --> 20:41.405
From...
[ sighs ]

20:43.542 --> 20:46.077
...From being
a foster child.

20:46.079 --> 20:48.212
Am I right,
or am I right?

20:48.214 --> 20:51.082
Sharon, could that young lady
have hidden her identity?

20:51.084 --> 20:52.717
From what I read,

20:52.719 --> 20:56.354
Gender identity dysphoria
in children is not a choice.

20:56.356 --> 20:57.855
Hmm.
Pancakes?

20:57.857 --> 21:00.391
Oh, um, yes, thank you.
She only wants one.

21:00.393 --> 21:03.160
Who eats
only one pancake?
Uh, your wife.

21:04.096 --> 21:05.463
[ cellphone chimes ]

21:05.465 --> 21:07.398
Uh-oh. Incoming.

21:07.400 --> 21:08.766
It's just kris.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.301
We're reading "romeo and juliet"
right now.

21:10.303 --> 21:12.136
We both missed it
in 9th grade,

21:12.138 --> 21:14.105
And I-I think
it's making her emotional.

21:14.107 --> 21:17.141
So,
are you two dating now?

21:17.143 --> 21:18.976
Rusty: No, no.
We're just hanging out.

21:18.978 --> 21:23.147
I mean, I like her a lot,
but it's -- it's hard to date

21:23.149 --> 21:25.383
When I have to take
a police escort everywhere I go.

21:25.385 --> 21:27.051
[ chuckles ]

21:27.053 --> 21:28.586
Excuse me. You know what?
I'm gonna need to move, so...

21:28.588 --> 21:30.821
Uh, oh, you've got it.
Okay, thanks.

21:30.823 --> 21:32.056
Mm-hmm.

21:35.093 --> 21:39.830
I thought you told me he'd been
hustling men on the street.

21:39.832 --> 21:41.132
Is he not gay?

21:41.134 --> 21:42.833
He hasn't told me
anything about that,

21:42.835 --> 21:44.635
And I am not asking.

21:44.637 --> 21:45.970
Maybe he's confused.

21:45.972 --> 21:47.805
I could help him
sort out his priorities.

21:47.807 --> 21:50.174
Listen, I only told you about
the    <i>abu</i>that he went through

21:50.176 --> 21:53.010
So that <i>you</i> could be
sensitive to his issues,

21:53.012 --> 21:56.013
Not so that you could push him
in one direction or the other.

21:56.015 --> 21:57.481
I never push people.
You spent virtually no time

21:57.483 --> 21:59.817
With our children
when they were rusty's age.

21:59.819 --> 22:02.119
Why are you
so interested in him?

22:02.121 --> 22:05.089
Look, I am brutally aware that
I am not a good parent, sharon,

22:05.091 --> 22:08.926
But it's not necessary
to remind me every five minutes.

22:08.928 --> 22:10.695
Oh, it is.

22:10.697 --> 22:16.167
Well, maybe I'm interested
in the kid because you are.

22:16.169 --> 22:18.336
I wish that you would
develop the same interest

22:18.338 --> 22:20.004
In finding yourself
an apartment.

22:29.681 --> 22:32.016
There was no wreck on the 101,
captain,

22:32.018 --> 22:33.317
But even if
there had been,

22:33.319 --> 22:34.552
I checked with
mr. Brand's office,

22:34.554 --> 22:36.153
And he took
the whole afternoon off.

22:36.155 --> 22:37.988
So, why'd he lie?

22:37.990 --> 22:39.457
Well, maybe he spent
the day getting ready
to kill his daughter.

22:39.459 --> 22:40.491
Murders take planning.

22:40.493 --> 22:41.692
[ door buzzes ]

22:41.694 --> 22:43.294
He seems to love her.

22:43.296 --> 22:46.197
Maybe too much.
Oh, god.
Let's not go there.

22:49.067 --> 22:50.735
I traced a credit check

22:50.737 --> 22:53.337
From a landlord in santa monica
to mr. Brand.

22:53.339 --> 22:55.206
He signed the lease
for a one-bedroom apartment

22:55.208 --> 22:56.841
The day of the murder.

22:56.843 --> 22:58.476
What else
is he covering up?

22:58.478 --> 23:02.480
He moved money out of
his bank account -- $80,000.

23:02.482 --> 23:06.650
And he ordered furniture
for the new place online.

23:06.652 --> 23:09.487
I need some way to ask mr. Brand
about these things,

23:09.489 --> 23:11.756
But first
I'm gonna shake him up.

23:11.758 --> 23:13.691
How?

23:13.693 --> 23:18.028
By giving him
what he asked for.

23:18.030 --> 23:19.997
Flynn: You sure
you want to do this, sir?

23:19.999 --> 23:22.767
'cause who you see in there
is not gonna be your daughter,

23:22.769 --> 23:24.568
And that image
is gonna be stuck in your head

23:24.570 --> 23:27.671
For the rest
of your life.

23:27.673 --> 23:31.175
Have you ever
lost a child?

23:31.177 --> 23:33.411
[ sighs ]
not exactly.

23:33.413 --> 23:35.846
Well, then you probably
wouldn't understand.

23:39.918 --> 23:43.154
[ sighs ]

23:54.299 --> 23:57.535
[ breathes deeply ]

24:09.915 --> 24:11.715
What happened?

24:14.085 --> 24:16.854
Her head was crushed in
with a baseball bat.

24:26.331 --> 24:29.166
[ sobbing ]

24:29.168 --> 24:34.104
[ crying ]
my baby.

24:34.106 --> 24:37.508
Does he look like
he's bluffing to you?

24:37.510 --> 24:39.143
No,
he looks guilty.

24:39.145 --> 24:44.415
A lot of murderers fall apart
when they see their victims.

24:44.417 --> 24:46.517
John: What in god's name
are you implying?

24:46.519 --> 24:48.686
You think renting that apartment
means -- means what?

24:48.688 --> 24:50.421
That I was having an affair --
is that it?

24:50.423 --> 24:51.822
We don't know
what to think.

24:51.824 --> 24:53.624
Maybe you can tell us
who the apartment was for.

24:53.626 --> 24:55.693
[ sighs ]

24:55.695 --> 24:56.827
It was for
me and michelle.

24:56.829 --> 24:58.629
Flynn:
You two were planning on

24:58.631 --> 25:01.465
Moving in together across town,
away from your wife?

25:01.467 --> 25:03.667
I was renting the apartment
to establish residency

25:03.669 --> 25:05.936
So michelle could go to
high school in santa monica.

25:05.938 --> 25:07.705
After that lewis kid
attacked her at the mall,

25:07.707 --> 25:09.106
She begged me
to let her start over

25:09.108 --> 25:10.841
Someplace where
nobody knew her.

25:10.843 --> 25:12.877
Did your wife
know about this?

25:12.879 --> 25:17.081
I signed the lease
the day that michelle was...

25:18.617 --> 25:22.353
I planned on -- on...
Telling my wife, but then I...

25:22.355 --> 25:24.121
[ sighs ]

25:34.466 --> 25:37.334
Oh, god, time has come
to a complete stop.

25:37.336 --> 25:40.104
Do you know that?

25:41.840 --> 25:44.975
No,
you don't know that,

25:44.977 --> 25:46.544
'cause you're all
running around,

25:46.546 --> 25:48.312
Doing this and doing that,
but for me,

25:48.314 --> 25:50.814
The world has completely stopped
spinning, and I'm just...

25:50.816 --> 25:52.650
Stuck in
this one horrible moment,

25:52.652 --> 25:53.918
This one terrible mistake.

25:53.920 --> 25:57.421
[ sighs ]

25:57.423 --> 25:59.323
What were you
asking about?

25:59.325 --> 26:01.859
My apartment. That's right.
[ sniffles ]

26:01.861 --> 26:03.494
I didn't tell my wife

26:03.496 --> 26:05.396
Because she already thought
michelle was spoiled.

26:05.398 --> 26:07.598
I was just thinking about
how to say it.

26:07.600 --> 26:08.866
What about the money?

26:08.868 --> 26:10.668
What money?

26:12.203 --> 26:14.438
Oh, I gave, uh --

26:14.440 --> 26:16.840
Gave them the security deposit
and the first month's rent.

26:16.842 --> 26:18.842
You also cashed in
your joint-retirement account.

26:18.844 --> 26:21.211
You took $80,000
out of the bank.

26:21.213 --> 26:23.514
That was for michelle.

26:23.516 --> 26:26.450
For michelle?
Were you planning on
telling your wife about that?

26:26.452 --> 26:28.619
Not right away, because
she was very much against

26:28.621 --> 26:30.354
What we were gonna do
with the money.

26:30.356 --> 26:32.790
What were you going to do?

26:32.792 --> 26:36.594
Hormone-replacement therapy
is very expensive --

26:36.596 --> 26:39.296
I mean, very, very,
very, very expensive.

26:39.298 --> 26:42.733
And it's not just that
insurance doesn't cover it.

26:42.735 --> 26:47.771
It's the whole idea of shooting
a tsunami of hormones --

26:47.773 --> 26:49.940
Hormones from
the opposite sex --

26:49.942 --> 26:54.545
Into my son's beautiful body
before he started puberty.

26:54.547 --> 26:55.913
Would you do that?

26:55.915 --> 26:58.449
How much money
was this going to take?

26:58.451 --> 27:00.484
Michael would have developed
breasts and hips,

27:00.486 --> 27:02.486
And it's permanent.

27:02.488 --> 27:05.923
That's a huge decision
for a 13-year-old.

27:05.925 --> 27:07.224
How much?

27:07.226 --> 27:10.294
$75,000.

27:10.296 --> 27:14.665
Now, I know that
michael wanted to transition,

27:14.667 --> 27:17.067
But that's a lot of money
for an otherwise healthy child,

27:17.069 --> 27:19.169
And who knows what
the long-term effects would be?

27:19.171 --> 27:20.604
I didn't want him
to do it.

27:20.606 --> 27:24.775
I just wanted him
to wait until he turned 21

27:24.777 --> 27:26.644
And his judgment
was better.

27:26.646 --> 27:28.312
Does that make me
a bad mother?

27:29.948 --> 27:31.148
No.

27:31.150 --> 27:34.451
But to me, this shovel

27:34.453 --> 27:39.890
Brings your parenting skills
into serious question.

27:43.528 --> 27:45.029
That's not mine.

27:45.031 --> 27:47.164
Strange -- we found it
in the trunk of your car.

27:47.166 --> 27:49.600
Your fingerprints
are all over the handle.

27:52.370 --> 27:54.638
That's because I borrowed it
from the office.

27:54.640 --> 27:56.206
I'm a realtor.

27:56.208 --> 27:58.976
I used it to plant
a "for sale" sign the other day.

27:58.978 --> 28:00.177
Where?

28:00.179 --> 28:01.879
New listing,
not far from our house.

28:01.881 --> 28:03.380
Why is that important?

28:03.382 --> 28:05.716
'cause the dirt
on the blade of this shovel

28:05.718 --> 28:07.985
Matches the dirt
in your daughter's grave.

28:07.987 --> 28:10.788
And the dirt
on these shoes of yours --

28:10.790 --> 28:13.624
It also matches the dirt
from your daughter's grave.

28:13.626 --> 28:15.559
That's probably because

28:15.561 --> 28:18.062
The house
that I told you about --

28:18.064 --> 28:19.897
It backs right up
to the park.

28:19.899 --> 28:22.633
And I'm not a geologist
or whatever,

28:22.635 --> 28:24.435
But I bet that's why
the dirt is the same.

28:26.404 --> 28:30.507
You know, that's a really
good explanation, mrs. Brand.

28:30.509 --> 28:33.343
Now, could you also explain
how you know

28:33.345 --> 28:35.179
That your daughter
was buried in the park?

28:35.181 --> 28:38.649
Because
we never told you that.

28:43.521 --> 28:48.125
You -- you said,
uh -- you...

28:51.062 --> 28:54.398
Mrs. Brand, we have arrived at
that point in our relationship

28:54.400 --> 28:58.235
That the lying has to end.

29:05.944 --> 29:10.547
I am a good mother.

29:10.549 --> 29:12.182
I'm a good mother.

29:13.785 --> 29:18.255
[ voice breaking ]
I'm a good mother.

29:20.358 --> 29:22.893
And I want a lawyer.

29:22.895 --> 29:24.561
You'll need one.

29:24.563 --> 29:26.296
Because as of this moment,

29:26.298 --> 29:28.866
You are under arrest
for murder in the first degree.

29:39.711 --> 29:42.646
Tao:
S.I.D. Says the girl's phone
was wiped clean.

29:42.648 --> 29:44.982
How clean?
Let's put it this way --

29:44.984 --> 29:47.785
The texts are gone forever,
and they might have been useful.

29:47.787 --> 29:49.286
You'd like
"shakespeare in love."

29:49.288 --> 29:51.288
I cannot believe
you haven't seen it yet.

29:51.290 --> 29:52.589
It's such a good movie.

29:52.591 --> 29:53.924
It's basically
"romeo and juliet"

29:53.926 --> 29:55.292
Crossed with
"twelfth night."

29:55.294 --> 29:56.727
Rusty:
Okay, so, explain to me

29:56.729 --> 29:58.562
How two boring plays
make one good movie.

29:58.564 --> 30:00.297
Shut up.

30:00.299 --> 30:01.431
It's playing at that place
you like -- hollywood forever.

30:01.433 --> 30:03.233
Oh,
you mean "the graveyard"?

30:03.235 --> 30:05.102
Yeah. Rusty says
they take these movies

30:05.104 --> 30:06.970
And project them
onto this big wall --

30:06.972 --> 30:08.672
Kind of like
a drive-in movie theater,

30:08.674 --> 30:10.808
Only without the cars.

30:10.810 --> 30:12.609
Everyone brings blankets
and lawn chairs.

30:12.611 --> 30:14.478
And pot.
And beer.

30:14.480 --> 30:15.979
Actually,
it's more of a wine crowd.

30:15.981 --> 30:17.748
And not everyone
partakes.

30:17.750 --> 30:18.949
I don't.

30:18.951 --> 30:20.350
Ah, quoth the girl
in the cop shop.

30:20.352 --> 30:22.019
Hi, rusty.

30:22.021 --> 30:23.253
Rusty: Hey, emma.

30:23.255 --> 30:25.088
Have --
have you met my, um...

30:26.424 --> 30:27.825
Kris?

30:27.827 --> 30:31.695
Kris, this is
the always-creepy emma rios.

30:31.697 --> 30:33.664
Creepy emma, kris.

30:33.666 --> 30:35.432
Hi.
She's the prosecutor

30:35.434 --> 30:38.502
In that murder trial
I'm supposed to testify in --

30:38.504 --> 30:40.604
The one who's basically
wrecking my life.

30:40.606 --> 30:42.206
You were doing a good job of
that before I ever showed up.

30:42.208 --> 30:43.640
Rusty.
Jack.

30:43.642 --> 30:45.943
Emma, I believe
the captain is expecting us.

30:49.848 --> 30:52.549
And that lady's the reason why
I can't go with you

30:52.551 --> 30:54.284
To see
"shakespeare in love,"

30:54.286 --> 30:56.320
Unless you want to hang with
the really popular kid

30:56.322 --> 30:58.121
Who brings a police escort
to the movies.

30:58.123 --> 30:59.690
I'm sure the potheads
would love that.

30:59.692 --> 31:02.392
All right. Time to study.
This way.

31:02.394 --> 31:06.396
And it doesn't help anything
to call emma "creepy."

31:06.398 --> 31:07.998
Aw, poor little kris.

31:08.000 --> 31:10.234
"love looks not with the eyes
but with the mind,

31:10.236 --> 31:13.470
And therefore is
wing'd cupid painted blind."

31:13.472 --> 31:15.038
Sir?

31:15.040 --> 31:18.242
You're weird.
I am, indeed, detective,

31:18.244 --> 31:20.744
And thus,
I take my leave of you.

31:20.746 --> 31:23.714
Emma: There's nothing unique
about that shovel.

31:23.716 --> 31:25.048
Provenza: I'll tell you
what's unique about it --

31:25.050 --> 31:27.317
Her prints
are all over it.

31:27.319 --> 31:28.485
Is that unique enough?
You can buy a shovel like that
at any hardware store --

31:28.487 --> 31:30.320
That's what
her lawyer will say.

31:30.322 --> 31:31.555
Well, what will her lawyer say
about the dirt from the grave

31:31.557 --> 31:32.756
That's on the shovel,
on her shoes?

31:32.758 --> 31:34.091
He'll say
what you already know --

31:34.093 --> 31:35.759
That you can't prove
when the dirt got there,

31:35.761 --> 31:38.095
And he'll go out and prove
that the dirt does not have

31:38.097 --> 31:40.063
The unique qualities we need,
and it won't.

31:40.065 --> 31:41.498
Couldn't you have waited
a little longer until she --

31:41.500 --> 31:43.433
No.
We pushed her to lawyer up.

31:43.435 --> 31:45.335
Now, here we are.
Let's review.

31:45.337 --> 31:46.536
Right.

31:46.538 --> 31:48.505
Her daughter's body
was buried

31:48.507 --> 31:51.341
In the same position
that the kid probably slept in.

31:51.343 --> 31:53.043
No, no,
don't you dare turn away.

31:53.045 --> 31:55.045
Now, you want this case,
you grow up,

31:55.047 --> 31:58.081
And you look at these pictures
side by side.

32:06.291 --> 32:08.425
You know they'll
put the victim on trial --

32:08.427 --> 32:12.462
The girl in the boy's body,
the gender bender, the misfit --

32:12.464 --> 32:14.798
How much trouble she was
to her mom.

32:14.800 --> 32:16.266
Where's hobbs?

32:16.268 --> 32:17.467
Captain, for the love of god,
call hobbs.

32:17.469 --> 32:19.269
It only takes one vote,
one juror,

32:19.271 --> 32:21.705
To ruin the entire case.

32:21.707 --> 32:26.276
I'd like a prosecutor
who isn't afraid of
losing in a good cause.

32:26.278 --> 32:28.111
Emma...

32:28.113 --> 32:33.550
Emma, y-you think I understand
boys who think they're girls?

32:34.986 --> 32:38.789
I'm just as much at sea
as your jurors will be,

32:38.791 --> 32:43.293
But I know when a kid has
had his head bashed in.

32:43.295 --> 32:46.997
Now, capt-- captain, are --
are you even listening to me?

32:46.999 --> 32:49.333
Mm.
What are you looking at?

32:49.335 --> 32:50.767
Phone records.

32:50.769 --> 32:53.236
Phone records?
What about phone records?

32:55.506 --> 32:57.240
Kids don't call.
They text.

32:57.242 --> 32:59.643
The only person that rusty calls
on his cellphone is me.

32:59.645 --> 33:05.515
Kris, he texts.
And?

33:05.517 --> 33:08.018
I promise you,
mr. Brand,

33:08.020 --> 33:10.988
We can prove
beyond a shadow of a doubt

33:10.990 --> 33:12.756
That your wife
buried your daughter.

33:12.758 --> 33:14.791
I don't believe it.

33:14.793 --> 33:17.027
My wife could never,
ever murder her own child.

33:17.029 --> 33:18.195
It's impossible.

33:18.197 --> 33:19.629
Yeah,
mom didn't kill michelle.

33:19.631 --> 33:21.131
We all loved michelle.

33:21.133 --> 33:24.968
Is that why you keep
calling her cellphone, matt,

33:24.970 --> 33:26.203
Even though
you know she's dead?

33:26.205 --> 33:27.637
Provenza:
But you didn't call her --

33:27.639 --> 33:29.106
Not a single time --

33:29.108 --> 33:30.974
The entire month
before she died.

33:30.976 --> 33:33.944
You texted each other a lot,
but you never called.

33:33.946 --> 33:35.812
Until night before last,

33:35.814 --> 33:40.617
When you dialed your sister's
number over 100 times in a row,

33:40.619 --> 33:42.686
Before you supposedly knew
she was missing.

33:42.688 --> 33:43.854
Why?

33:43.856 --> 33:45.789
I think I know why.

33:45.791 --> 33:48.658
Your mother was in the park,
looking for michelle's body,

33:48.660 --> 33:52.696
Hunting for where you left it,
by following the ringtone.

33:52.698 --> 33:53.864
Is that
how it happened?

33:53.866 --> 33:55.766
What are you saying?
Mr. Brand.

33:56.868 --> 33:58.335
[ dial tone, dialing ]

33:58.337 --> 34:00.070
And yesterday and today,
you've gone on calling

34:00.072 --> 34:01.638
Because you miss
the sound of her voice.

34:01.640 --> 34:02.672
Is that it?

34:02.674 --> 34:04.074
Michelle:
<i>Hey, everybody,</i>

34:04.076 --> 34:05.175
<i>If you're</i>
<i>talking to this phone,</i>

34:05.177 --> 34:06.877
<i>You must be somebody I love.</i>

34:06.879 --> 34:08.145
<i>If you love me back,</i>
<i>leave me a lovely message.</i>

34:08.147 --> 34:09.413
<i>Bye.</i>
<i>[</i>  <i>beep</i>]

34:09.415 --> 34:11.214
[ inhales deeply ]

34:11.216 --> 34:13.650
Matt, you want to tell us
what happened now,

34:13.652 --> 34:15.719
Or do you want your mother
to sit in jail

34:15.721 --> 34:17.320
For the rest of her life?

34:17.322 --> 34:19.890
What reason would my wife have
for killing our daughter?

34:19.892 --> 34:21.258
[ voice breaking ]
maybe because

34:21.260 --> 34:22.726
You and michelle
were leaving us.

34:22.728 --> 34:25.862
Maybe because mom
didn't want you to move out.

34:25.864 --> 34:27.664
No, no.

34:27.666 --> 34:31.501
Your mother didn't even
know about that.

34:33.404 --> 34:36.573
Oh, my god.

34:36.575 --> 34:37.874
Matthew?

34:37.876 --> 34:39.509
Sharon:
Michelle called the house.

34:39.511 --> 34:42.179
Your mom was making dinner,
and you got into the car,

34:42.181 --> 34:44.881
And    <i>y</i>went to the mall
to pick her up.

34:44.883 --> 34:46.917
What have you done?

34:46.919 --> 34:49.853
Yeah, I picked her up.

34:55.026 --> 34:56.193
Dad and I
are moving to santa monica.

34:56.195 --> 34:57.461
Matt:
She told me all about

34:57.463 --> 34:58.895
Your little apartment
in santa monica.

34:58.897 --> 35:00.464
It's true. We're moving,

35:00.466 --> 35:02.432
And I'm gonna start
at santa monica high school.

35:02.434 --> 35:03.633
The kids there
are so cool.

35:03.635 --> 35:05.702
She was all happy.

35:05.704 --> 35:08.438
She was excited
about tearing our family apart.

35:08.440 --> 35:12.042
Dad's moving out?
Are they getting a divorce?

35:12.044 --> 35:13.577
That's why she wanted
to go to the mall.

35:13.579 --> 35:15.112
She wanted to say goodbye
to her friends.

35:15.114 --> 35:17.114
I don't know. I mean,
who cares if they get a divorce?

35:17.116 --> 35:19.816
She said, "I don't care
if they get a divorce."

35:19.818 --> 35:22.252
We weren't divorcing.
She was just changing schools!

35:22.254 --> 35:24.087
She was destroying
everything!

35:24.089 --> 35:25.789
I'm supposed to
lose my family

35:25.791 --> 35:27.924
Because
she wants hormone shots?

35:27.926 --> 35:29.593
Matt.
Everything --

35:29.595 --> 35:34.664
Everything has always, always,
always been about her.

35:34.666 --> 35:37.501
It's been like
living in an insane asylum

35:37.503 --> 35:39.269
From the moment
she was born.

35:39.271 --> 35:40.837
So you put a stop to it.

35:40.839 --> 35:43.406
I mean, if you had seen
the expression on her face

35:43.408 --> 35:45.308
When she told me
that you two were leaving.

35:45.310 --> 35:47.477
God, why is everything
always about you?

35:47.479 --> 35:49.813
Why can't you
be happy for me?
She thought
I'd be happy for her.

35:49.815 --> 35:52.582
That's how crazy selfish
she was.

35:52.584 --> 35:54.451
All those years
explaining her,

35:54.453 --> 35:56.953
Protecting her,
and I'd had it.

35:56.955 --> 35:58.021
Just let me out.

35:59.624 --> 36:01.758
I pulled the car over,
and she got out...

36:07.098 --> 36:10.667
...And ran toward the park.

36:10.669 --> 36:12.669
I chased her.

36:12.671 --> 36:14.771
With a bat?
With a bat.

36:30.688 --> 36:31.955
I hit her with it.

36:34.725 --> 36:35.792
And then
after you killed her?

36:35.794 --> 36:37.727
I wasn't trying to do that.

36:37.729 --> 36:39.696
Oh, yes, you were.

36:39.698 --> 36:42.232
You hit her in the head
three times.

36:42.234 --> 36:44.467
You <i>did</i> mean it.

36:44.469 --> 36:46.336
And then you went home
and you told your mom.

36:46.338 --> 36:48.238
Sykes: And she went out
and buried michelle.

36:48.240 --> 36:50.140
And took the battery
from her phone.

36:50.142 --> 36:52.709
Hoping we wouldn't find her --
hoping to protect you.

36:52.711 --> 36:55.378
Well, maybe -- maybe --
maybe she thought

36:55.380 --> 36:58.148
That we could just go back
to being a regular family again.

36:58.150 --> 37:00.550
[ sighs ]

37:00.552 --> 37:02.485
[ voice breaking ] you chased
your little sister down,

37:02.487 --> 37:05.255
And you beat her to death
with a bat?

37:05.257 --> 37:07.824
Yeah, I chased her.

37:10.027 --> 37:12.362
And you know what,
dad?

37:12.364 --> 37:15.165
What?

37:15.167 --> 37:19.669
She didn't run
like a girl.

37:26.510 --> 37:30.547
Okay, matt.

37:30.549 --> 37:33.717
We've already
arrested your mother,

37:33.719 --> 37:35.685
And to let her go --
and so she can't continue

37:35.687 --> 37:37.520
To act as if she's the one
who did this --

37:37.522 --> 37:42.192
I need you to tell me...

37:42.194 --> 37:44.027
Where'd you put the bat?

38:14.759 --> 38:17.861
Just one more thing
to do.

38:32.009 --> 38:34.411
I didn't murder her.
[ sighs ]

38:34.413 --> 38:37.681
No.
You murdered her family.

38:37.683 --> 38:39.449
You made it your mission

38:39.451 --> 38:42.018
To make this kid
feel like a monster,

38:42.020 --> 38:43.486
But you're the monster.

38:43.488 --> 38:46.289
And do you know what we do
to monsters, lewis?

38:46.291 --> 38:47.924
Kill them
with a pitchfork?

38:47.926 --> 38:51.194
That would be great,
but as it is,

38:51.196 --> 38:52.662
We can only lock them up
in jail,

38:52.664 --> 38:54.097
Which is where you're going
till you turn 18.

38:54.099 --> 38:55.332
What the hell
are you talking about?

38:55.334 --> 38:56.933
I didn't do anything
to this freak.

38:56.935 --> 38:58.501
Not true.

38:58.503 --> 39:01.037
These pictures prove that
you committed sexual battery,

39:01.039 --> 39:02.939
Which is good enough
to put you away in juvie.

39:02.941 --> 39:05.308
What? You can't.
You can't -- you can't do that.

39:05.310 --> 39:06.409
I can.

39:08.346 --> 39:11.781
And, hey,
have a miserable life.

39:13.951 --> 39:16.653
Michelle:
<i>Hey, everybody,</i>

39:16.655 --> 39:18.154
<i>If you're</i>
<i>talking to this phone,</i>

39:18.156 --> 39:19.856
<i>You must be somebody I love.</i>

39:19.858 --> 39:20.557
<i>If you love me back,</i>
<i>leave me a lovely message.</i>

39:20.559 --> 39:21.691
<i>Bye.</i>

39:21.693 --> 39:23.526
[  <i>beep</i>]

39:47.385 --> 39:49.018
[ sniffles ]

39:49.020 --> 39:51.020
[ chuckling ] oh, oh, oh.

39:51.022 --> 39:53.223
I just had
another flash

39:53.225 --> 39:56.259
Of what I modestly call
"genius."

39:56.261 --> 40:00.263
He has.
What better, what safer,
what more trustworthy cop

40:00.265 --> 40:02.866
To accompany our young students
of "romeo and juliet"

40:02.868 --> 40:04.267
To the movies than you?

40:04.269 --> 40:06.336
Tonight?

40:06.338 --> 40:08.772
Mm-hmm.
They're showing
"shakespeare in love"

40:08.774 --> 40:10.073
At hollywood forever.

40:10.075 --> 40:12.409
Blankets, picnic,
mistaken identities,

40:12.411 --> 40:14.711
Romance, role reversals,
outrageous fortune.

40:14.713 --> 40:18.515
The kids really want to go,
but they can't without you.

40:18.517 --> 40:20.517
What say you, madam?

40:20.519 --> 40:22.252
Kris?

40:22.254 --> 40:24.287
My parents are okay
as long as I'm home by 11:00.

40:24.289 --> 40:25.855
Easy-peasy.

40:25.857 --> 40:28.691
I can transport
our young juliet home,

40:28.693 --> 40:32.195
And you can return romeo
here to his own balcony.

40:34.698 --> 40:37.033
It sounds like
a lot of fun.

40:38.068 --> 40:40.069
Doesn't it?

40:40.071 --> 40:41.771
Okay.

40:41.773 --> 40:44.140
Everyone wants to go.
Let's go.

40:44.142 --> 40:46.276
All right, whoa!
Tallyho. Let's go.

40:46.278 --> 40:47.343
[ chuckles ]

40:49.246 --> 40:50.880
[ chuckles ]

40:50.882 --> 40:54.284
Hey, it's just like
old times, eh?

40:54.286 --> 40:56.786
Yeah, really,
really old times.

40:56.788 --> 40:58.555
Elizabethan, I think.

40:59.957 --> 41:02.792
Tell me something --
was this your idea or rusty's?

41:02.794 --> 41:06.396
Oh,
we're in it together,

41:06.398 --> 41:09.599
And at our core,
we're really all alike.

41:09.601 --> 41:10.800
Right?

41:18.809 --> 41:21.678
We should hurry.

41:21.680 --> 41:24.247
The cemetery
fills up early.
